The government yesterday launched a drive meant to improve drug safety. The Regional Medicine Regulatory Harmonisation project was launched by Health CAS Rashid Aman at a Nairobi hotel. Pharmacy and Poisons Board member Rugendo Birichi represented the Cabinet Administrative Secretary. He said PROFORMA grant is a joint venture by experts from academia, the national medicines regulatory authorities and WHO-collaborating centres and regional centres of excellence. Aman said the government is committed to providing safe, quality and effective medical products and health technologies. It will strengthen the vigilance systems to ensure patientsâ€™ safety, he said. The initiative will involve increasing the number of clinical trials and promoting large-scale mass drug administration and immunisation programmes to ensure better products and ensure better treatment results. Click here for latest political news 